# Legwork configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `config` (same directory) and edit. `config` is gitignored.
# scripts/legwork_runner.py loads it at startup, so launchd (which does not
# read your shell profile), cron and manual runs share one source of truth.
# Real environment variables always override the file. Values may use $HOME
# and ~, which are expanded. Lines are KEY=VALUE; # starts a comment.
#
# You can also point the runner at a config elsewhere with LEGWORK_CONFIG=/path.

# Where the legwork repo lives. Default: $HOME/legwork.
LEGWORK_DIR=$HOME/legwork

# Autonomous fires per project per calendar day. Default: 8. Counted from
# runner.log, so truncating or rotating that file resets the day's count.
LEGWORK_DAILY_CAP=8

# Optional spend guard, in dollars. Unset or 0 means no cost cap. When set,
# the runner sums today's per-fire costs from runner.log and stops firing for
# the rest of the day once the cap is reached (alerting once, like a stall).
# LEGWORK_DAILY_COST_CAP=10

# --- Review pipeline (OPTIONAL) ---------------------------------------------
# The n8n webhooks the SessionEnd hook and the runner post to. Leave BOTH unset
# to run the queue with no reviewer: the runner still fires sessions and they
# still wrap, the review post and the Telegram alerts are just skipped.
#   LEGWORK_WEBHOOK_URL  receives session evidence for review.
#   LEGWORK_ALERT_URL    receives runner stall alerts and the daily heartbeat.
# LEGWORK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n-host/webhook/legwork-review
# LEGWORK_ALERT_URL=https://your-n8n-host/webhook/legwork-alert

# --- Claude config dirs (OPTIONAL) ------------------------------------------
# Run autonomous sessions under a dedicated Claude config dir, so they never
# inherit whatever account your interactive shell defaults to. Leave unset to
# use the default config. A project may set `account: <name>` in its
# frontmatter; set CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR_<NAME> (uppercased) to give that account
# its own config dir.
# CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=$HOME/.claude-legwork
# CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR_WORK=$HOME/.claude-legwork-work

# --- Applied outside the runner (documented here so config lives in one place)
# REVIEWER_MODEL is read by reviewer/n8n-build-node.js (the model the reviewer
# call uses). Set it there, or wherever you paste that node. Default:
# claude-sonnet-4-6.
# REVIEWER_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
#
# The launchd tick interval lives in scripts/com.legwork.runner.plist
# (StartInterval, seconds). Default: 300 (every 5 minutes).
